phase-7.log — Phase 7: Spec Audit

=== Forensic entry (2026-07-09) ===

Final comprehensive audit of the Go coding-agent harness completed.

Deliverables:
1. docs/full-spec-audit-violations.md (documented findings)
2. docs/full-spec-audit-fix-plan.md (remediation plan)

Key findings:
- Dogfooding step (spec §16) remains outstanding.
- Git branching history divergence noted (spec §15).
- Bash path-scoping limitation requires system-prompt-level warning (§6.1).
- Audit process requires transition from manual to automated (spec §14).

No critical violations found; the harness is functionally sound and satisfies the core spec requirements. The findings are primarily documentation, audit-process improvements, and one outstanding rollout task (dogfooding).

Ready for final project close-out.

=== Architect entry — Fix Cycle 1 (2026-07-09) ===

ADR updated from "Proposed" to "Accepted". Added Fix Cycle 1 section specifying:
1. --audit-phase N: remove stub, load forensic config, build user prompt from
   forensic-per-phase-audit-template.md (replace {N}), enforce read-only tool
   restriction (read_file + list_dir + write_log only), fall through to common
   turn-loop path. Log to phase-N.log.
2. --audit-full: same pattern but user prompt from forensic-full-audit.md
   (verbatim). Log to full-audit.log.
3. --agent prompt-generator --spec path: remove stub, load prompt-generator
   config, set user prompt referencing spec path, fall through to common path
   with existing tool restrictions (no override needed).

Zero changes to internal/ packages. Purely cmd/harness/main.go wiring.
e2e/audit_e2e_test.go needs integration-test guard. See ADR for full spec.

=== Builder entry — Fix Cycle 1 (2026-07-09) ===

Implemented all three CLI modes as real turn-loop invocations:

--audit-phase N: removed stub (was print+os.Exit). Now loads forensic agent
config, reads .aa/forensic-per-phase-audit-template.md, replaces {N} with
phase number, enforces read-only tool restrictions (read_file, list_dir,
write_log only — no edit_file, no create_file, no bash_exec), and falls
through to the common execution path. Logs to phase-N.log.

--audit-full: same pattern using .aa/forensic-full-audit.md verbatim. Logs
to full-audit.log. Tool restriction same as --audit-phase.

--agent prompt-generator --spec path: removed stub (was print+os.Exit). Now
loads prompt-generator config, constructs user prompt referencing spec path
(agent reads the file itself via read_file, per project convention), and
falls through to the common path. Uses prompt-generator's own tool config
(read + restricted create_file + list_dir + write_log) — no override needed.

Files changed:
  cmd/harness/main.go      — removed 3 early-exit stubs, added mode routing
                             + mutual exclusion check (--audit-phase +
                             --audit-full conflict), added audit read-only
                             tool override after ParseAgentConfig
  e2e/audit_e2e_test.go    — binary-level test now guarded by
                             HARNESS_INTEGRATION_TEST=1 env var; added 5
                             unit-level tests using Fake LLM: tool
                             restriction verification, turn loop execution
                             with audit/prompt-generator configs, and
                             template substitution verification

Zero changes to internal/ packages. All internal tests pass.
Build: go build ./cmd/harness/ clean.
All 3 CLI modes confirmed to compile and route correctly.

